class.description:
This MO describes the Active Alarm List. This list contains a momentary listing of all problems in the system for which a stateful alarm has been sent but not yet been cleared. The Active Alarm List file is written to the file named by attribute fileName. The text file with the Active Alarms in the cluster has the following format: - The first line is the header and consists of attribute names separated by semicolons. - Each following line contains one alarm. - Each line consists of alarm attribute values separated by semicolons.
The following is an example of a text file containing two active alarms:
DN;MajorType;MinorType;AdditionalText;Severity;SpecificProblem;SequenceNumber;EventTime;Stateful;EventType;ProbableCause ManagedElement=1,MyApp=1,Logging=1;193;123456789;"Device (/dev/sda5) is 95% full, log level raised to critical";5;MyApp Log Level Raised;2;12656565656;1;1;418; ManagedElement=1,MyApp=1,Pm=1;193;987654321;"Could not find script /opt/myscript.sh";4;MyApp PM Data Collect Error;3;12656565656;1;1;418;
